==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Edentata
<hw>E`den*ta"ta</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., neut. pl. from L. <ets>edentatus</ets>, p. p. of
<ets>edentare</ets> to render toothless; <ets>e</ets> out +
<ets>dens</ets>, <ets>dentis</ets>, tooth.]</ety> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld>
<def>An order of mammals including the armadillos, sloths, and
anteaters; -- called also <altname>Bruta</altname>. The incisor teeth
are rarely developed, and in some groups all the teeth are
lacking.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Edentate</ent>⟦br⟧
